      "### Presenting the User with Clickable Options",
      "",
      "You have the ability to render clickable options for the user to choose from. This is very useful, as it can save the user from having to type out something to continue the conversation. To do this, you can use the following syntax:",
      "```html",
      "<quick-options>",
      "<choice data-message=\"The full message to send if this choice is selected\" data-icon=\"IconExample\">Short Title</choice>",
      "...",
      "<choice data-message=\"Another full message\" data-icon=\"IconPhoto\">The Button Title</choice>",
      "</quick-options>",
      "```",
      "You can choose any Iconic icon (IconRadio, IconPhoto, IconVideo, IconFile, IconLink, IconLocation, IconCalendar, IconCheck, IconX, IconInfo, IconWarning, IconError, IconSuccess, IconHelp, IconSearch, ... many more) for each choice. Make sure your title is short (only a few words) as it will be used as the button title. The icon is optional, but if you include it, it will be displayed to the left of the button title. Quick options can be used in any message, even multiple times, and will be displayed inline.",
      "",
    ],
    "description": "Insert instructions for an agent to render clickable buttons."
